Capstone Project: SmartHub

This repository contains the source code for the Capstone smart home application developed using React Native and Expo.

Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

Node.js (v12 or newer)
npm (which comes with Node.js)
Expo CLI

You can install Expo CLI globally with npm:
npm install -g expo-cli

Setting Up the Development Environment
To set up your development environment, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:
git clone Capstone

Navigate to the project directory:
cd capstone

Install the dependencies:
npm install

Running the Application
To start the Expo development server:
npm start


Libraries and Dependencies
This project makes use of several notable libraries:

@react-navigation: For handling navigation between screens.
axios: For making API calls.
expo: An open-source platform for making universal native apps with React.
firebase: For the backend and real-time database operations.
formik: For building forms.
react-native-paper: For material design components.
react-native-chart-kit: For rendering charts.
react-native-vector-icons: For displaying icons.
